    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n### Description\nEscaped register inputs such as:\n- \\\\\\<Return\\>\n- \\\\\\<Esc\\>\n\n... are being printed as chars '^M' and '^[' when macros are run from input mode as opposed to executing RETURN or ESC keyboard events. \n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean`\n`:let @x=\"-----\\<Return>\"`\n\n(In input mode) \n`<c-R> x`\n\nOutput will be: \n`-----^M`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEscape characters for Esc and Return should be treated as the corresponding keys, as opposed to printing the string literal char codes. \n\nI have a lot of macros that take things from the clipboard and reformat them automatically. In the current build, they are all broken due the macros printing the chars instead of moving between input mode and normal mode. \n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo. vim 9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMacOS 26.4.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm2 3.6.10\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256colour\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew",
